# pyrrm Development Guidelines

This project is a Python rainfall-runoff modeling library (`pyrrm`) that provides:
- Multiple rainfall-runoff models (Sacramento, GR4J, GR5J, GR6J)
- Flexible calibration framework (PyDREAM, NumPyro NUTS, SCE-UA, SciPy)
- Numba JIT-compiled kernels for 30–70x faster model execution
- Batch and multi-catchment network calibration
- 48-metric canonical diagnostic suite
- Sensitivity analysis using Sobol methods
- Comprehensive visualization tools (Matplotlib and Plotly)
- CalibrationReport export to Excel / CSV

